        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 3:54PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 354 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Cooper Heights, or near
Trenton, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Lafayette, Trenton, Fort Oglethorpe, Chickamauga, La Fayette,
Chattanooga Valley, Naomi, Noble, Blue Spring, Linwood, Boynton,
Beaumont, New England, Chattanooga  Valley, Cloudland Canyon State
Park, Cooper Heights, Rock Spring, Rising Fawn, and Fairview.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
